'''''Magnum opus''''' (sometimes ''Opus magnum''), from the [[Latin]] meaning ''great work'', refers to the best or most renowned achievement of an [[author]], [[artist]], or [[composer]]. It can also refer to an individual literary or artistic masterpiece. no less, walk on earth, water, and fire
the elements compose a magnum opus
my modus is operandi is amalgam


